<ns1974:section xmlns:ns1974="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.javaBeans.exercises.exercises">
  <ns1975:title xmlns:ns1975="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Exercises</ns1975:title>
  <ns1976:para xmlns:ns1976="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1977:orderedlist xmlns:ns1977="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns1978:listitem xmlns:ns1978="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1979:para xmlns:ns1979="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        Develop a Java Beans implementation with state change notification for the following class
        graph (preferably draw a UML diagram first) :
        <ns1980:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1980="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1981:listitem xmlns:ns1981="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1982:para xmlns:ns1982="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            A media play list has a name and a collection of tracks via composition and an
            association to a person object which encapsulates the name and e-mail address of the
            person who compiled the play list. The track list provides services to add and remove
            tracks. 
          </ns1982:para></ns1981:listitem>
          <ns1983:listitem xmlns:ns1983="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1984:para xmlns:ns1984="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            A track can be a raw track or a marked up track which is a specialization of a raw track.
          </ns1984:para></ns1983:listitem>
          <ns1985:listitem xmlns:ns1985="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1986:para xmlns:ns1986="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            Raw tracks have a name and a duration. 
          </ns1986:para></ns1985:listitem>
          <ns1987:listitem xmlns:ns1987="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1988:para xmlns:ns1988="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            Marked up tracks have via composition a Markup object which 
            contains fields for track name, composer and artist.          
            They also have one or more categories via aggregation.
            A track may be, for example, assigned to three categories, 
            <ns1989:literal xmlns:ns1989="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">instrumental</ns1989:literal>, <ns1990:literal xmlns:ns1990="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">20'th century</ns1990:literal> 
            and<ns1991:literal xmlns:ns1991="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">classical</ns1991:literal>. 
          </ns1988:para></ns1987:listitem>
        </ns1980:itemizedlist>
        In this example make use of 
        <ns1992:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1992="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1993:listitem xmlns:ns1993="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1994:para xmlns:ns1994="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            interfaces providing mutable and immutable views onto objects,
          </ns1994:para></ns1993:listitem>
          <ns1995:listitem xmlns:ns1995="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1996:para xmlns:ns1996="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            inner classes,
          </ns1996:para></ns1995:listitem>
          <ns1997:listitem xmlns:ns1997="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1998:para xmlns:ns1998="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            static nested classes, and
          </ns1998:para></ns1997:listitem>
          <ns1999:listitem xmlns:ns1999="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2000:para xmlns:ns2000="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            exception handling.
          </ns2000:para></ns1999:listitem>
        </ns1992:itemizedlist>
        
         
        <ns2001:itemizedlist xmlns:ns2001="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns2002:listitem xmlns:ns2002="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2003:para xmlns:ns2003="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            Interfaces
          </ns2003:para></ns2002:listitem>
        </ns2001:itemizedlist>
        
      </ns1979:para></ns1978:listitem>
    </ns1977:orderedlist>
  </ns1976:para>
</ns1974:section>